news_comment <- raw_news_comment %>%
  mutate(reply = str_replace_all(reply, "[^-]", " "), #      
         reply = str_squish(reply)) %>%                   #   
  distinct(reply, .keep_all = T) %>%                      #    / .keep_all = T :    
  filter(str_count(reply, boundary("word")) >= 3)         # 3      ->

comment <- news_comment %>%                               #        in 2-2-1
  unnest_tokens(input = reply,                            #     
                output = word,                            #  
                token = extractNoun,                      #   
                drop = F) %>%                             #   X
  filter(str_count(word) > 1) %>%                         # 1     
  group_by(id) %>%                                        #  id   ->       
  distinct(word, .keep_all = T) %>%                       #    / .keep_all = T :    
  ungroup() %>%                                           #  
  select(id, word)                                        #  id word

count_word_doc <- count_word %>%                           #      in 2-2-4
  count(id, word, sort = T)                                #     

# 1-2. DTM 
dtm_comment <- count_word_doc %>%                          #        
  # DTM 
  cast_dtm(document = id,                                  #   
           term = word,                                    #   
           value = n)                                      #    

# 1-3. LDA 
lda_model <- LDA(dtm_comment,                              # DTM in 2-3-1 
                 k = 8,                                    #  
                 method = "Gibbs",                         #   :  
                 control = list(seed = 1234))              # Seed  ->    


# 2.    
# 2-1. beta 
term_topic <- tidy(lda_model,                              # LDA   
                   matrix = "beta")                        # beta 

# 2-2.  beta    
top_term_topic <- term_topic %>%                           # beta     
  group_by(topic) %>%                                      #  topic   ->  beta     
  slice_max(beta, n = 10)                                  # beta    10

# 3-1. gamma

                  matrix = "gamma")                       # gamma 

# 3-2.       
doc_class <- doc_topic %>%                                # gamma     
  group_by(document) %>%                                  #  document   ->  gamma      
  slice_max(gamma, n = 1)                                 # gamma    1  

# 3-3.
